<br>
If Time was truely instanced, this wouldn't matter.  <br>
<br>
What is wrong with a model where if you CAN kill time, time is available for you to kill?<br>
<br>
It used to be that the bottlenecks were created by the need to gear up.  You needed Thurg armor to be able to do HoT.  You needed HoT drops to be ready for Kael/NToV.  You needed NToV to be able to more into Ssra and eventually VT, and you needed VT to be able to get into elementals.  The gear needs necessitated that every guild in the server wasn't after the same content.<br>
<br>
The increase in levels and AA abilities has changed this.  Just THINK what will happen when the level cap goes to 70 if time isn't fully instanced.  What a grand clusterfuck that is going to be. <p><p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=365770> <center><img src="http://www.geocities.com/latuttle/harmsig2.jpg"></center> </img> </a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=reynaldofl>ReynaldoFL</A></span><br> Posts: 98<br> <font color=#330000>(5/28/04 1:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19425.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's old is new again...</span><hr size=1> Np, just stretch out Coir / Rathe spawn times to 6.5 instead of 3.5 days hee haw.<br>
